29/01/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- Transport ministers from the Southeast European Co-operation Process countries signed a memorandum calling for a new rail network to link the major hubs of the region, Greece's Transport and Communications Ministry announced on Friday (27 January). As part of the agreement, participants pledged to upgrade their national rail systems, increase the speed of rail transportation, and make other improvements. The first phase of the project is to be completed by 2013, and the second phase in 2020. (ANA, MPA - 27/01/06)
